Facades.Name: Action
Facades.Doc: ActionAPI implements the client API for interacting with Actions

Methods.Name: Actions
Methods.Doc:
Actions takes a list of ActionTags, and returns the full Action for
each ID.

Methods.Name: ApplicationsCharmsActions
Methods.Doc:
ApplicationsCharmsActions returns a slice of charm Actions for a slice of
services.

Methods.Name: Cancel
Methods.Doc: Cancel attempts to cancel enqueued Actions from running.

Methods.Name: Enqueue
Methods.Doc:
Enqueue takes a list of Actions and queues them up to be executed by
the designated ActionReceiver, returning the params.Action for each
enqueued Action, or an error if there was a problem enqueueing the
Action.

Methods.Name: FindActionTagsByPrefix
Methods.Doc:
FindActionTagsByPrefix takes a list of string prefixes and finds
corresponding ActionTags that match that prefix.

Methods.Name: ListAll
Methods.Doc:
ListAll takes a list of Entities representing ActionReceivers and
returns all of the Actions that have been enqueued or run by each of
those Entities.

Methods.Name: ListCompleted
Methods.Doc:
ListCompleted takes a list of Entities representing ActionReceivers
and returns all of the Actions that have been run on each of those
Entities.

Methods.Name: ListPending
Methods.Doc:
ListPending takes a list of Entities representing ActionReceivers
and returns all of the Actions that are enqueued for each of those
Entities.

Methods.Name: ListRunning
Methods.Doc:
ListRunning takes a list of Entities representing ActionReceivers and
returns all of the Actions that have are running on each of those
Entities.

Methods.Name: Run
Methods.Doc:
Run the commands specified on the machines identified through the
list of machines, units and services.

Methods.Name: RunOnAllMachines
Methods.Doc: RunOnAllMachines attempts to run the specified command on all the machines.

Facades.Name: Addresser
Facades.Doc: AddresserAPI provides access to the Addresser API facade.

Methods.Name: CanDeallocateAddresses
Methods.Doc:
CanDeallocateAddresses checks if the current environment can
deallocate IP addresses.

Methods.Name: CleanupIPAddresses
Methods.Doc: CleanupIPAddresses releases and removes the dead IP addresses.

Methods.Name: WatchIPAddresses
Methods.Doc: WatchIPAddresses observes changes to the IP addresses.

Facades.Name: Agent
Facades.Doc: AgentAPIV2 implements the version 2 of the API provided to an agent.

Methods.Name: ClearReboot
Methods.Doc: ClearReboot will clear the reboot flag on provided machines, if it exists.

Methods.Name: ControllerConfig
Methods.Doc: ControllerConfig returns the controller's configuration.

Methods.Name: ModelConfig
Methods.Doc: ModelConfig returns the current environment's configuration.

Methods.Name: SetPasswords
Methods.Doc: SetPasswords sets the given password for each supplied entity, if possible.

Methods.Name: WatchForModelConfigChanges
Methods.Doc:
WatchForModelConfigChanges returns a NotifyWatcher that observes
changes to the environment configuration.
Note that although the NotifyWatchResult contains an Error field,
it's not used because we are only returning a single watcher,
so we use the regular error return.

Facades.Name: AgentTools
Facades.Doc: AgentToolsAPI implements the API used by the machine model worker.

Methods.Name: UpdateToolsAvailable
Methods.Doc:
UpdateToolsAvailable invokes a lookup and further update in environ
for new patches of the current tool versions.

Facades.Name: AllModelWatcher
Facades.Doc:
SrvAllWatcher defines the API methods on a state.Multiwatcher.
which watches any changes to the state. Each client has its own
current set of watchers, stored in resources. It is used by both
the AllWatcher and AllModelWatcher facades.

Facades.Name: AllWatcher
Facades.Doc:
SrvAllWatcher defines the API methods on a state.Multiwatcher.
which watches any changes to the state. Each client has its own
current set of watchers, stored in resources. It is used by both
the AllWatcher and AllModelWatcher facades.

Facades.Name: Annotations
Facades.Doc:
API implements the service interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: Get
Methods.Doc:
Get returns annotations for given entities.
If annotations cannot be retrieved for a given entity, an error is returned.
Each entity is treated independently and, hence, will fail or succeed independently.

Methods.Name: Set
Methods.Doc: Set stores annotations for given entities

Facades.Name: Application
Facades.Doc:
API implements the application interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: AddRelation
Methods.Doc: AddRelation adds a relation between the specified endpoints and returns the relation info.

Methods.Name: AddUnits
Methods.Doc: AddUnits adds a given number of units to an application.

Methods.Name: CharmRelations
Methods.Doc: CharmRelations implements the server side of Application.CharmRelations.

Methods.Name: Deploy
Methods.Doc:
Deploy fetches the charms from the charm store and deploys them
using the specified placement directives.

Methods.Name: Destroy
Methods.Doc: Destroy destroys a given application.

Methods.Name: DestroyRelation
Methods.Doc: DestroyRelation removes the relation between the specified endpoints.

Methods.Name: DestroyUnits
Methods.Doc: DestroyUnits removes a given set of application units.

Methods.Name: Expose
Methods.Doc:
Expose changes the juju-managed firewall to expose any ports that
were also explicitly marked by units as open.

Methods.Name: Get
Methods.Doc: Get returns the configuration for a service.

Methods.Name: GetCharmURL
Methods.Doc:
GetCharmURL returns the charm URL the given application is
running at present.

Methods.Name: GetConstraints
Methods.Doc: GetConstraints returns the constraints for a given application.

Methods.Name: Set
Methods.Doc:
Set implements the server side of Application.Set.
It does not unset values that are set to an empty string.
Unset should be used for that.

Methods.Name: SetCharm
Methods.Doc: SetCharm sets the charm for a given for the application.

Methods.Name: SetConstraints
Methods.Doc: SetConstraints sets the constraints for a given application.

Methods.Name: SetMetricCredentials
Methods.Doc: SetMetricCredentials sets credentials on the application.

Methods.Name: Unexpose
Methods.Doc:
Unexpose changes the juju-managed firewall to unexpose any ports that
were also explicitly marked by units as open.

Methods.Name: Unset
Methods.Doc: Unset implements the server side of Client.Unset.

Methods.Name: Update
Methods.Doc:
Update updates the application attributes, including charm URL,
minimum number of units, settings and constraints.
All parameters in params.ApplicationUpdate except the application name are optional.

Facades.Name: ApplicationScaler
Facades.Doc: Facade allows model-manager clients to watch and rescale services.

Methods.Name: Rescale
Methods.Doc:
Rescale causes any supplied services to be scaled up to their
minimum size.

Methods.Name: Watch
Methods.Doc:
Watch returns a watcher that sends the names of services whose
unit count may be below their configured minimum.

Facades.Name: Backups
Facades.Doc: API serves backup-specific API methods.

Methods.Name: Create
Methods.Doc:
Create is the API method that requests juju to create a new backup
of its state.  It returns the metadata for that backup.

Methods.Name: FinishRestore
Methods.Doc: FinishRestore implements the server side of Backups.FinishRestore.

Methods.Name: Info
Methods.Doc: Info provides the implementation of the API method.

Methods.Name: List
Methods.Doc: List provides the implementation of the API method.

Methods.Name: PrepareRestore
Methods.Doc: PrepareRestore implements the server side of Backups.PrepareRestore.

Methods.Name: Restore
Methods.Doc: Restore implements the server side of Backups.Restore.

Facades.Name: Block
Facades.Doc:
API implements Block interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: List
Methods.Doc: List implements Block.List().

Methods.Name: SwitchBlockOff
Methods.Doc: SwitchBlockOff implements Block.SwitchBlockOff().

Methods.Name: SwitchBlockOn
Methods.Doc: SwitchBlockOn implements Block.SwitchBlockOn().

Facades.Name: CharmRevisionUpdater
Facades.Doc:
CharmRevisionUpdaterAPI implements the CharmRevisionUpdater interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: UpdateLatestRevisions
Methods.Doc:
UpdateLatestRevisions retrieves the latest revision information from the charm store for all deployed charms
and records this information in state.

Facades.Name: Charms
Facades.Doc:
API implements the charms interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: CharmInfo
Methods.Doc: CharmInfo returns information about the requested charm.

Methods.Name: IsMetered
Methods.Doc: IsMetered returns whether or not the charm is metered.

Methods.Name: List
Methods.Doc:
List returns a list of charm URLs currently in the state.
If supplied parameter contains any names, the result will be filtered
to return only the charms with supplied names.

Facades.Name: Cleaner
Facades.Doc: CleanerAPI implements the API used by the cleaner worker.

Methods.Name: Cleanup
Methods.Doc: Cleanup triggers a state cleanup

Methods.Name: WatchCleanups
Methods.Doc: WatchChanges watches for cleanups to be perfomed in state

Facades.Name: Client
Facades.Doc: Client serves client-specific API methods.

Methods.Name: APIHostPorts
Methods.Doc: APIHostPorts returns the API host/port addresses stored in state.

Methods.Name: AbortCurrentUpgrade
Methods.Doc:
AbortCurrentUpgrade aborts and archives the current upgrade
synchronisation record, if any.

Methods.Name: AddCharmWithAuthorization
Methods.Doc:
AddCharmWithAuthorization adds the given charm URL (which must include revision) to
the model, if it does not exist yet. Local charms are not
supported, only charm store URLs. See also AddLocalCharm().

The authorization macaroon, args.CharmStoreMacaroon, may be
omitted, in which case this call is equivalent to AddCharm.

Methods.Name: AddMachines
Methods.Doc: AddMachines adds new machines with the supplied parameters.

Methods.Name: AddMachinesV2
Methods.Doc: AddMachinesV2 adds new machines with the supplied parameters.

Methods.Name: AgentVersion
Methods.Doc: AgentVersion returns the current version that the API server is running.

Methods.Name: CharmInfo
Methods.Doc: CharmInfo returns information about the requested charm.

Methods.Name: DestroyMachines
Methods.Doc: DestroyMachines removes a given set of machines.

Methods.Name: DestroyModel
Methods.Doc:
DestroyModel will try to destroy the current model.
If there is a block on destruction, this method will return an error.

Methods.Name: FindTools
Methods.Doc: FindTools returns a List containing all tools matching the given parameters.

Methods.Name: FullStatus
Methods.Doc: FullStatus gives the information needed for juju status over the api

Methods.Name: GetBundleChanges
Methods.Doc:
GetBundleChanges returns the list of changes required to deploy the given
bundle data. The changes are sorted by requirements, so that they can be
applied in order.

Methods.Name: GetModelConstraints
Methods.Doc: GetModelConstraints returns the constraints for the model.

Methods.Name: InjectMachines
Methods.Doc: InjectMachines injects a machine into state with provisioned status.

Methods.Name: ModelGet
Methods.Doc:
ModelGet implements the server-side part of the
get-model-config CLI command.

Methods.Name: ModelInfo
Methods.Doc:
ModelInfo returns information about the current model (default
series and type).

Methods.Name: ModelSet
Methods.Doc:
ModelSet implements the server-side part of the
set-model-config CLI command.

Methods.Name: ModelUnset
Methods.Doc:
ModelUnset implements the server-side part of the
set-model-config CLI command.

Methods.Name: ModelUserInfo
Methods.Doc: ModelUserInfo returns information on all users in the model.

Methods.Name: PrivateAddress
Methods.Doc: PrivateAddress implements the server side of Client.PrivateAddress.

Methods.Name: ProvisioningScript
Methods.Doc:
ProvisioningScript returns a shell script that, when run,
provisions a machine agent on the machine executing the script.

Methods.Name: PublicAddress
Methods.Doc: PublicAddress implements the server side of Client.PublicAddress.

Methods.Name: ResolveCharms
Methods.Doc:
ResolveCharm resolves the best available charm URLs with series, for charm
locations without a series specified.

Methods.Name: Resolved
Methods.Doc: Resolved implements the server side of Client.Resolved.

Methods.Name: RetryProvisioning
Methods.Doc: RetryProvisioning marks a provisioning error as transient on the machines.

Methods.Name: SetModelAgentVersion
Methods.Doc: SetModelAgentVersion sets the model agent version.

Methods.Name: SetModelConstraints
Methods.Doc: SetModelConstraints sets the constraints for the model.

Methods.Name: StatusHistory
Methods.Doc: StatusHistory returns a slice of past statuses for several entities.

Facades.Name: Controller
Facades.Doc:
ControllerAPI implements the environment manager interface and is
the concrete implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: AllModels
Methods.Doc:
AllModels allows controller administrators to get the list of all the
environments in the controller.

Methods.Name: ControllerConfig
Methods.Doc: ControllerConfig returns the controller's configuration.

Methods.Name: DestroyController
Methods.Doc:
DestroyController will attempt to destroy the controller. If the args
specify the removal of blocks or the destruction of the models, this
method will attempt to do so.

If the controller has any non-Dead hosted models, then an error with
the code params.CodeHasHostedModels will be transmitted, regardless of
the value of the DestroyModels parameter. This is to inform the client
that it should wait for hosted models to be completely cleaned up
before proceeding.

Methods.Name: InitiateModelMigration
Methods.Doc:
InitiateModelMigration attempts to begin the migration of one or
more models to other controllers.

Methods.Name: ListBlockedModels
Methods.Doc:
ListBlockedModels returns a list of all environments on the controller
which have a block in place.  The resulting slice is sorted by environment
name, then owner. Callers must be controller administrators to retrieve the
list.

Methods.Name: ModelConfig
Methods.Doc:
ModelConfig returns the environment config for the controller
environment.  For information on the current environment, use
client.ModelGet

Methods.Name: ModelStatus
Methods.Doc: ModelStatus returns a summary of the environment.

Methods.Name: RemoveBlocks
Methods.Doc: RemoveBlocks removes all the blocks in the controller.

Methods.Name: WatchAllModels
Methods.Doc:
WatchAllModels starts watching events for all models in the
controller. The returned AllWatcherId should be used with Next on the
AllModelWatcher endpoint to receive deltas.

Facades.Name: Deployer
Facades.Doc: DeployerAPI provides access to the Deployer API facade.

Methods.Name: APIAddresses
Methods.Doc: APIAddresses returns the list of addresses used to connect to the API.

Methods.Name: APIHostPorts
Methods.Doc: APIHostPorts returns the API server addresses.

Methods.Name: CACert
Methods.Doc: CACert returns the certificate used to validate the state connection.

Methods.Name: ConnectionInfo
Methods.Doc:
ConnectionInfo returns all the address information that the
deployer task needs in one call.

Methods.Name: Life
Methods.Doc: Life returns the life status of every supplied entity, where available.

Methods.Name: ModelUUID
Methods.Doc:
ModelUUID returns the model UUID to connect to the environment
that the current connection is for.

Methods.Name: Remove
Methods.Doc:
Remove removes every given entity from state, calling EnsureDead
first, then Remove. It will fail if the entity is not present.

Methods.Name: SetPasswords
Methods.Doc: SetPasswords sets the given password for each supplied entity, if possible.

Methods.Name: StateAddresses
Methods.Doc: StateAddresses returns the list of addresses used to connect to the state.

Methods.Name: WatchAPIHostPorts
Methods.Doc: WatchAPIHostPorts watches the API server addresses.

Methods.Name: WatchUnits
Methods.Doc:
WatchUnits starts a StringsWatcher to watch all units belonging to
to any entity (machine or service) passed in args.

Facades.Name: DiscoverSpaces
Facades.Doc: DiscoverSpacesAPI implements the API used by the discoverspaces worker.

Methods.Name: AddSubnets
Methods.Doc: AddSubnets is defined on the API interface.

Methods.Name: CreateSpaces
Methods.Doc:
CreateSpaces creates a new Juju network space, associating the
specified subnets with it (optional; can be empty).

Methods.Name: ListSpaces
Methods.Doc: ListSpaces lists all the available spaces and their associated subnets.

Methods.Name: ListSubnets
Methods.Doc:
ListSubnets lists all the available subnets or only those matching
all given optional filters.

Methods.Name: ModelConfig
Methods.Doc: ModelConfig returns the current model's configuration.

Facades.Name: DiskManager
Facades.Doc: DiskManagerAPI provides access to the DiskManager API facade.

Facades.Name: EntityWatcher
Facades.Doc:
srvEntitiesWatcher defines the API for methods on a state.StringsWatcher.
Each client has its own current set of watchers, stored in resources.
srvEntitiesWatcher notifies about changes for all entities of a given kind,
sending the changes as a list of strings, which could be transformed
from state entity ids to their corresponding entity tags.

Methods.Name: Next
Methods.Doc:
Next returns when a change has occured to an entity of the
collection being watched since the most recent call to Next
or the Watch call that created the srvEntitiesWatcher.

Methods.Name: Stop
Methods.Doc: Stop stops the watcher.

Facades.Name: FilesystemAttachmentsWatcher
Facades.Doc:
srvMachineStorageIdsWatcher defines the API wrapping a state.StringsWatcher
watching machine/storage attachments. This watcher notifies about storage
entities (volumes/filesystems) being attached to and detached from machines.

TODO(axw) state needs a new watcher, this is a bt of a hack. State watchers
could do with some deduplication of logic, and I don't want to add to that
spaghetti right now.

Methods.Name: Next
Methods.Doc:
Next returns when a change has occured to an entity of the
collection being watched since the most recent call to Next
or the Watch call that created the srvMachineStorageIdsWatcher.

Methods.Name: Stop
Methods.Doc: Stop stops the watcher.

Facades.Name: Firewaller
Facades.Doc: FirewallerAPI provides access to the Firewaller API facade.

Methods.Name: ControllerConfig
Methods.Doc: ControllerConfig returns the controller's configuration.

Methods.Name: GetAssignedMachine
Methods.Doc:
GetAssignedMachine returns the assigned machine tag (if any) for
each given unit.

Methods.Name: GetExposed
Methods.Doc: GetExposed returns the exposed flag value for each given service.

Methods.Name: GetMachineActiveSubnets
Methods.Doc:
GetMachineActiveSubnets returns the tags of the all subnets that each machine
(in args) has open ports on.

Methods.Name: GetMachinePorts
Methods.Doc:
GetMachinePorts returns the port ranges opened on a machine for the specified
subnet as a map mapping port ranges to the tags of the units that opened
them.

Methods.Name: InstanceId
Methods.Doc:
InstanceId returns the provider specific instance id for each given
machine or an CodeNotProvisioned error, if not set.

Methods.Name: Life
Methods.Doc: Life returns the life status of every supplied entity, where available.

Methods.Name: ModelConfig
Methods.Doc: ModelConfig returns the current environment's configuration.

Methods.Name: Watch
Methods.Doc: Watch starts an NotifyWatcher for each given entity.

Methods.Name: WatchForModelConfigChanges
Methods.Doc:
WatchForModelConfigChanges returns a NotifyWatcher that observes
changes to the environment configuration.
Note that although the NotifyWatchResult contains an Error field,
it's not used because we are only returning a single watcher,
so we use the regular error return.

Methods.Name: WatchModelMachines
Methods.Doc:
WatchModelMachines returns a StringsWatcher that notifies of
changes to the life cycles of the top level machines in the current
model.

Methods.Name: WatchOpenedPorts
Methods.Doc:
WatchOpenedPorts returns a new StringsWatcher for each given
environment tag.

Methods.Name: WatchUnits
Methods.Doc:
WatchUnits starts a StringsWatcher to watch all units belonging to
to any entity (machine or service) passed in args.

Facades.Name: HighAvailability
Facades.Doc:
HighAvailabilityAPI implements the HighAvailability interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: ResumeHAReplicationAfterUpgrade
Methods.Doc:
ResumeHAReplicationAfterUpgrade will add the upgraded members of HA
cluster to the upgraded master.

Methods.Name: StopHAReplicationForUpgrade
Methods.Doc:
StopHAReplicationForUpgrade will prompt the HA cluster to enter upgrade
mongo mode.

Facades.Name: HostKeyReporter
Facades.Doc: Facade implements the API required by the hostkeyreporter worker.

Methods.Name: ReportKeys
Methods.Doc: ReportKeys sets the SSH host keys for one or more entities.

Facades.Name: ImageManager
Facades.Doc:
ImageManagerAPI implements the ImageManager interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: DeleteImages
Methods.Doc: DeleteImages deletes the images matching the specified filter.

Methods.Name: ListImages
Methods.Doc: ListImages returns images matching the specified filter.

Facades.Name: ImageMetadata
Facades.Doc:
API is the concrete implementation of the api end point
for loud image metadata manipulations.

Methods.Name: Delete
Methods.Doc:
Delete deletes cloud image metadata for given image ids.
It supports bulk calls.

Methods.Name: List
Methods.Doc:
List returns all found cloud image metadata that satisfy
given filter.
Returned list contains metadata ordered by priority.

Methods.Name: Save
Methods.Doc:
Save stores given cloud image metadata.
It supports bulk calls.

Methods.Name: UpdateFromPublishedImages
Methods.Doc:
UpdateFromPublishedImages retrieves currently published image metadata and
updates stored ones accordingly.

Facades.Name: InstancePoller
Facades.Doc: InstancePollerAPI provides access to the InstancePoller API facade.

Methods.Name: AreManuallyProvisioned
Methods.Doc:
AreManuallyProvisioned returns whether each given entity is
manually provisioned or not. Only machine tags are accepted.

Methods.Name: ControllerConfig
Methods.Doc: ControllerConfig returns the controller's configuration.

Methods.Name: InstanceId
Methods.Doc:
InstanceId returns the provider specific instance id for each given
machine or an CodeNotProvisioned error, if not set.

Methods.Name: InstanceStatus
Methods.Doc:
InstanceStatus returns the instance status for each given entity.
Only machine tags are accepted.

Methods.Name: Life
Methods.Doc: Life returns the life status of every supplied entity, where available.

Methods.Name: ModelConfig
Methods.Doc: ModelConfig returns the current environment's configuration.

Methods.Name: ProviderAddresses
Methods.Doc:
ProviderAddresses returns the list of all known provider addresses
for each given entity. Only machine tags are accepted.

Methods.Name: SetInstanceStatus
Methods.Doc:
SetInstanceStatus updates the instance status for each given
entity. Only machine tags are accepted.

Methods.Name: SetProviderAddresses
Methods.Doc:
SetProviderAddresses updates the list of known provider addresses
for each given entity. Only machine tags are accepted.

Methods.Name: Status
Methods.Doc: Status returns the status of each given entity.

Methods.Name: WatchForModelConfigChanges
Methods.Doc:
WatchForModelConfigChanges returns a NotifyWatcher that observes
changes to the environment configuration.
Note that although the NotifyWatchResult contains an Error field,
it's not used because we are only returning a single watcher,
so we use the regular error return.

Methods.Name: WatchModelMachines
Methods.Doc:
WatchModelMachines returns a StringsWatcher that notifies of
changes to the life cycles of the top level machines in the current
model.

Facades.Name: KeyManager
Facades.Doc:
KeyManagerAPI implements the KeyUpdater interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: AddKeys
Methods.Doc: AddKeys adds new authorised ssh keys for the specified user.

Methods.Name: DeleteKeys
Methods.Doc: DeleteKeys deletes the authorised ssh keys for the specified user.

Methods.Name: ImportKeys
Methods.Doc: ImportKeys imports new authorised ssh keys from the specified key ids for the specified user.

Methods.Name: ListKeys
Methods.Doc: ListKeys returns the authorised ssh keys for the specified users.

Facades.Name: KeyUpdater
Facades.Doc:
KeyUpdaterAPI implements the KeyUpdater interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: AuthorisedKeys
Methods.Doc:
AuthorisedKeys reports the authorised ssh keys for the specified machines.
The current implementation relies on global authorised keys being stored in the environment config.
This will change as new user management and authorisation functionality is added.

Methods.Name: WatchAuthorisedKeys
Methods.Doc:
WatchAuthorisedKeys starts a watcher to track changes to the authorised ssh keys
for the specified machines.
The current implementation relies on global authorised keys being stored in the environment config.
This will change as new user management and authorisation functionality is added.

Facades.Name: LeadershipService
Facades.Doc:
LeadershipService implements a variant of leadership.Claimer for consumption
over the API.

Methods.Name: BlockUntilLeadershipReleased
Methods.Doc:
BlockUntilLeadershipReleased blocks the caller until leadership is
released for the given service.

Methods.Name: ClaimLeadership
Methods.Doc: ClaimLeadership makes a leadership claim with the given parameters.

Methods.Name: Life
Methods.Doc: Life returns the life status of every supplied entity, where available.

Methods.Name: Watch
Methods.Doc: Watch starts an NotifyWatcher for each given entity.

Facades.Name: Logger
Facades.Doc:
LoggerAPI implements the Logger interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: LoggingConfig
Methods.Doc: LoggingConfig reports the logging configuration for the agents specified.

Methods.Name: WatchLoggingConfig
Methods.Doc:
WatchLoggingConfig starts a watcher to track changes to the logging config
for the agents specified..  Unfortunately the current infrastruture makes
watching parts of the config non-trivial, so currently any change to the
config will cause the watcher to notify the client.

Facades.Name: MachineActions
Facades.Doc:
Facade implements the machineactions interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: Actions
Methods.Doc:
Actions returns the Actions by Tags passed and ensures that the machine asking
for them is the machine that has the actions

Methods.Name: BeginActions
Methods.Doc: BeginActions marks the actions represented by the passed in Tags as running.

Methods.Name: FinishActions
Methods.Doc: FinishActions saves the result of a completed Action

Methods.Name: RunningActions
Methods.Doc:
RunningActions lists the actions running for the entities passed in.
If we end up needing more than ListRunning at some point we could follow/abstract
what's done in the client actions package.

Methods.Name: WatchActionNotifications
Methods.Doc:
WatchActionNotifications returns a StringsWatcher for observing
incoming action calls to a machine.

Facades.Name: MachineManager
Facades.Doc: MachineManagerAPI provides access to the MachineManager API facade.

Methods.Name: AddMachines
Methods.Doc: AddMachines adds new machines with the supplied parameters.

Facades.Name: Machiner
Facades.Doc: MachinerAPI implements the API used by the machiner worker.

Methods.Name: APIAddresses
Methods.Doc: APIAddresses returns the list of addresses used to connect to the API.

Methods.Name: APIHostPorts
Methods.Doc: APIHostPorts returns the API server addresses.

Methods.Name: CACert
Methods.Doc: CACert returns the certificate used to validate the state connection.

Methods.Name: EnsureDead
Methods.Doc:
EnsureDead calls EnsureDead on each given entity from state. It
will fail if the entity is not present. If it's Alive, nothing will
happen (see state/EnsureDead() for units or machines).

Methods.Name: Jobs
Methods.Doc: Jobs returns the jobs assigned to the given entities.

Methods.Name: Life
Methods.Doc: Life returns the life status of every supplied entity, where available.

Methods.Name: ModelUUID
Methods.Doc:
ModelUUID returns the model UUID to connect to the environment
that the current connection is for.

Methods.Name: SetStatus
Methods.Doc: SetStatus sets the status of each given entity.

Methods.Name: UpdateStatus
Methods.Doc:
UpdateStatus updates the status data of each given entity.
TODO(fwereade): WTF. This method exists *only* for the convenience of the
*client* API -- and is itself completely broken -- but we still expose it
in every facade with a StatusSetter? FFS.

Methods.Name: Watch
Methods.Doc: Watch starts an NotifyWatcher for each given entity.

Methods.Name: WatchAPIHostPorts
Methods.Doc: WatchAPIHostPorts watches the API server addresses.

Facades.Name: MeterStatus
Facades.Doc:
MeterStatusAPI implements the MeterStatus interface and is the concrete implementation
of the API endpoint.

Methods.Name: GetMeterStatus
Methods.Doc: GetMeterStatus returns meter status information for each unit.

Methods.Name: WatchMeterStatus
Methods.Doc:
WatchMeterStatus returns a NotifyWatcher for observing changes
to each unit's meter status.

Facades.Name: MetricsAdder
Facades.Doc:
MetricsAdderAPI implements the metrics adder interface and is the concrete
implementation of the API end point.

Methods.Name: AddMetricBatches
Methods.Doc: AddMetricBatches implements the MetricsAdder interface.

Facades.Name: MetricsDebug
Facades.Doc:
MetricsDebugAPI implements the metricsdebug interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: GetMetrics
Methods.Doc: GetMetrics returns all metrics stored by the state server.

Methods.Name: SetMeterStatus
Methods.Doc: SetMeterStatus sets meter statuses for entities.

Facades.Name: MetricsManager
Facades.Doc:
MetricsManagerAPI implements the metrics manager interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: CleanupOldMetrics
Methods.Doc:
CleanupOldMetrics removes old metrics from the collection.
The single arg params is expected to contain and environment uuid.
Even though the call will delete all metrics across environments
it serves to validate that the connection has access to at least one environment.

Methods.Name: SendMetrics
Methods.Doc: SendMetrics will send any unsent metrics onto the metric collection service.

Facades.Name: MigrationFlag
Facades.Doc: Facade lets clients watch and get models' migration phases.

Methods.Name: Phase
Methods.Doc:
Phase returns the current migration phase or an error for every
supplied entity.

Methods.Name: Watch
Methods.Doc:
Watch returns an id for use with the NotifyWatcher facade, or an
error, for every supplied entity.

Facades.Name: MigrationMaster
Facades.Doc:
API implements the API required for the model migration
master worker.

Methods.Name: Export
Methods.Doc: Export serializes the model associated with the API connection.

Methods.Name: GetMigrationStatus
Methods.Doc:
GetMigrationStatus returns the details and progress of the latest
model migration.

Methods.Name: SetPhase
Methods.Doc:
SetPhase sets the phase of the active model migration. The provided
phase must be a valid phase value, for example QUIESCE" or
"ABORT". See the core/migration package for the complete list.

Methods.Name: Watch
Methods.Doc:
Watch starts watching for an active migration for the model
associated with the API connection. The returned id should be used
with the NotifyWatcher facade to receive events.

Facades.Name: MigrationMinion
Facades.Doc:
API implements the API required for the model migration
master worker.

Methods.Name: Watch
Methods.Doc:
Watch starts watching for status updates for a migration attempt
for the model. It will report when a migration starts and when its
status changes (including when it finishes). An initial event will
be fired if there has ever been a migration attempt for the model.

The MigrationStatusWatcher facade must be used to receive events
from the watcher.

Methods.Name: Next
Methods.Doc:
Next returns when the status for a model migration for the
associated model changes. The current details for the active
migration are returned.

Methods.Name: Stop
Methods.Doc: Stop stops the watcher.

Facades.Name: MigrationTarget
Facades.Doc:
API implements the API required for the model migration
master worker when communicating with the target controller.

Methods.Name: Abort
Methods.Doc:
Abort removes the specified model from the database. It is an error to
attempt to Abort a model that has a migration mode other than importing.

Methods.Name: Activate
Methods.Doc:
Activate sets the migration mode of the model to "active". It is an error to
attempt to Abort a model that has a migration mode other than importing.

Methods.Name: Import
Methods.Doc:
Import takes a serialized Juju model, deserializes it, and
recreates it in the receiving controller.

Facades.Name: ModelManager
Facades.Doc:
ModelManagerAPI implements the model manager interface and is
the concrete implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: ConfigSkeleton
Methods.Doc:
ConfigSkeleton returns config values to be used as a starting point for the
API caller to construct a valid model specific config.  The provider
and region params are there for future use, and current behaviour expects
both of these to be empty.

Methods.Name: CreateModel
Methods.Doc:
CreateModel creates a new model using the account and
model config specified in the args.

Methods.Name: ListModels
Methods.Doc:
ListModels returns the models that the specified user
has access to in the current server.  Only that controller owner
can list models for any user (at this stage).  Other users
can only ask about their own models.

Methods.Name: ModelInfo
Methods.Doc: ModelInfo returns information about the specified models.

Methods.Name: ModifyModelAccess
Methods.Doc: ModifyModelAccess changes the model access granted to users.

Facades.Name: NotifyWatcher
Facades.Doc:
srvNotifyWatcher defines the API access to methods on a state.NotifyWatcher.
Each client has its own current set of watchers, stored in resources.

Methods.Name: Next
Methods.Doc:
Next returns when a change has occurred to the
entity being watched since the most recent call to Next
or the Watch call that created the NotifyWatcher.

Methods.Name: Stop
Methods.Doc: Stop stops the watcher.

Facades.Name: Pinger
Facades.Doc: pinger describes a resource that can be pinged and stopped.

Facades.Name: Provisioner
Facades.Doc: ProvisionerAPI provides access to the Provisioner API facade.

Methods.Name: APIAddresses
Methods.Doc: APIAddresses returns the list of addresses used to connect to the API.

Methods.Name: APIHostPorts
Methods.Doc: APIHostPorts returns the API server addresses.

Methods.Name: CACert
Methods.Doc: CACert returns the certificate used to validate the state connection.

Methods.Name: Constraints
Methods.Doc: Constraints returns the constraints for each given machine entity.

Methods.Name: ContainerConfig
Methods.Doc:
ContainerConfig returns information from the environment config that is
needed for container cloud-init.

Methods.Name: ContainerManagerConfig
Methods.Doc:
ContainerManagerConfig returns information from the environment config that is
needed for configuring the container manager.

Methods.Name: ControllerConfig
Methods.Doc: ControllerConfig returns the controller's configuration.

Methods.Name: DistributionGroup
Methods.Doc:
DistributionGroup returns, for each given machine entity,
a slice of instance.Ids that belong to the same distribution
group as that machine. This information may be used to
distribute instances for high availability.

Methods.Name: EnsureDead
Methods.Doc:
EnsureDead calls EnsureDead on each given entity from state. It
will fail if the entity is not present. If it's Alive, nothing will
happen (see state/EnsureDead() for units or machines).

Methods.Name: FindTools
Methods.Doc: FindTools returns a List containing all tools matching the given parameters.

Methods.Name: GetContainerInterfaceInfo
Methods.Doc:
GetContainerInterfaceInfo returns information to configure networking
for a container. It accepts container tags as arguments. If the address
allocation feature flag is not enabled, it returns a NotSupported error.

Methods.Name: InstanceId
Methods.Doc:
InstanceId returns the provider specific instance id for each given
machine or an CodeNotProvisioned error, if not set.

Methods.Name: InstanceStatus
Methods.Doc:
InstanceStatus returns the instance status for each given entity.
Only machine tags are accepted.

Methods.Name: Life
Methods.Doc: Life returns the life status of every supplied entity, where available.

Methods.Name: MachinesWithTransientErrors
Methods.Doc:
MachinesWithTransientErrors returns status data for machines with provisioning
errors which are transient.

Methods.Name: ModelConfig
Methods.Doc: ModelConfig returns the current environment's configuration.

Methods.Name: ModelUUID
Methods.Doc:
ModelUUID returns the model UUID to connect to the environment
that the current connection is for.

Methods.Name: PrepareContainerInterfaceInfo
Methods.Doc:
PrepareContainerInterfaceInfo allocates an address and returns
information to configure networking for a container. It accepts
container tags as arguments. If the address allocation feature flag
is not enabled, it returns a NotSupported error.

Methods.Name: ProvisioningInfo
Methods.Doc: ProvisioningInfo returns the provisioning information for each given machine entity.

Methods.Name: ReleaseContainerAddresses
Methods.Doc:
ReleaseContainerAddresses finds addresses allocated to a container
and marks them as Dead, to be released and removed. It accepts
container tags as arguments. If address allocation feature flag is
not enabled, it will return a NotSupported error.

Methods.Name: Remove
Methods.Doc:
Remove removes every given entity from state, calling EnsureDead
first, then Remove. It will fail if the entity is not present.

Methods.Name: Series
Methods.Doc: Series returns the deployed series for each given machine entity.

Methods.Name: SetInstanceInfo
Methods.Doc:
SetInstanceInfo sets the provider specific machine id, nonce,
metadata and network info for each given machine. Once set, the
instance id cannot be changed.

Methods.Name: SetInstanceStatus
Methods.Doc:
SetInstanceStatus updates the instance status for each given
entity. Only machine tags are accepted.

Methods.Name: SetPasswords
Methods.Doc: SetPasswords sets the given password for each supplied entity, if possible.

Methods.Name: SetStatus
Methods.Doc: SetStatus sets the status of each given entity.

Methods.Name: SetSupportedContainers
Methods.Doc: SetSupportedContainers updates the list of containers supported by the machines passed in args.

Methods.Name: StateAddresses
Methods.Doc: StateAddresses returns the list of addresses used to connect to the state.

Methods.Name: Status
Methods.Doc: Status returns the status of each given entity.

Methods.Name: Tools
Methods.Doc: Tools finds the tools necessary for the given agents.

Methods.Name: UpdateStatus
Methods.Doc:
UpdateStatus updates the status data of each given entity.
TODO(fwereade): WTF. This method exists *only* for the convenience of the
*client* API -- and is itself completely broken -- but we still expose it
in every facade with a StatusSetter? FFS.

Methods.Name: WatchAPIHostPorts
Methods.Doc: WatchAPIHostPorts watches the API server addresses.

Methods.Name: WatchAllContainers
Methods.Doc:
WatchAllContainers starts a StringsWatcher to watch all containers deployed to
any machine passed in args.

Methods.Name: WatchContainers
Methods.Doc:
WatchContainers starts a StringsWatcher to watch containers deployed to
any machine passed in args.

Methods.Name: WatchForModelConfigChanges
Methods.Doc:
WatchForModelConfigChanges returns a NotifyWatcher that observes
changes to the environment configuration.
Note that although the NotifyWatchResult contains an Error field,
it's not used because we are only returning a single watcher,
so we use the regular error return.

Methods.Name: WatchMachineErrorRetry
Methods.Doc:
WatchMachineErrorRetry returns a NotifyWatcher that notifies when
the provisioner should retry provisioning machines with transient errors.

Methods.Name: WatchModelMachines
Methods.Doc:
WatchModelMachines returns a StringsWatcher that notifies of
changes to the life cycles of the top level machines in the current
model.

Methods.Name: ProxyConfig
Methods.Doc: ProxyConfig returns the proxy settings for the current environment

Methods.Name: WatchForProxyConfigAndAPIHostPortChanges
Methods.Doc: WatchForProxyConfigAndAPIHostPortChanges watches for cleanups to be perfomed in state

Facades.Name: Reboot
Facades.Doc: RebootAPI provides access to the Upgrader API facade.

Methods.Name: ClearReboot
Methods.Doc: ClearReboot will clear the reboot flag on provided machines, if it exists.

Methods.Name: GetRebootAction
Methods.Doc:
GetRebootAction returns the action a machine agent should take.
If a reboot flag is set on the machine, then that machine is
expected to reboot (params.ShouldReboot).
a reboot flag set on the machine parent or grandparent, will
cause the machine to shutdown (params.ShouldShutdown).
If no reboot flag is set, the machine should do nothing (params.ShouldDoNothing).

Methods.Name: RequestReboot
Methods.Doc: RequestReboot sets the reboot flag on the provided machines

Methods.Name: WatchForRebootEvent
Methods.Doc:
WatchForRebootEvent starts a watcher to track if there is a new
reboot request on the machines ID or any of its parents (in case we are a container).

Facades.Name: RelationUnitsWatcher
Facades.Doc:
srvRelationUnitsWatcher defines the API wrapping a state.RelationUnitsWatcher.
It notifies about units entering and leaving the scope of a RelationUnit,
and changes to the settings of those units known to have entered.

Methods.Name: Next
Methods.Doc:
Next returns when a change has occured to an entity of the
collection being watched since the most recent call to Next
or the Watch call that created the srvRelationUnitsWatcher.

Methods.Name: Stop
Methods.Doc: Stop stops the watcher.

Facades.Name: Resumer
Facades.Doc: ResumerAPI implements the API used by the resumer worker.

Facades.Name: RetryStrategy
Facades.Doc: RetryStrategyAPI implements RetryStrategy

Methods.Name: RetryStrategy
Methods.Doc:
RetryStrategy returns RetryStrategyResults that can be used by any code that uses
to configure the retry timer that's currently in juju utils.

Methods.Name: WatchRetryStrategy
Methods.Doc:
WatchRetryStrategy watches for changes to the environment. Currently we only allow
changes to the boolean that determines whether retries should be attempted or not.

Facades.Name: SSHClient
Facades.Doc: Facade implements the API required by the sshclient worker.

Methods.Name: PrivateAddress
Methods.Doc:
PrivateAddress reports the preferred private network address for one or
more entities. Machines and units are supported.

Methods.Name: Proxy
Methods.Doc:
Proxy returns whether SSH connections should be proxied through the
controller hosts for the model associated with the API connection.

Methods.Name: PublicAddress
Methods.Doc:
PublicAddress reports the preferred public network address for one
or more entities. Machines and units are suppored.

Methods.Name: PublicKeys
Methods.Doc:
PublicKeys returns the public SSH hosts for one or more
entities. Machines and units are supported.

Facades.Name: Singular
Facades.Doc:
Facade allows controller machines to request exclusive rights to administer
some specific model for a limited time.

Methods.Name: Claim
Methods.Doc:
Claim makes the supplied singular-controller lease requests. (In practice,
any requests not for the connection's model, or not on behalf of the
connected EnvironManager machine, will be rejected.)

Methods.Name: Wait
Methods.Doc:
Wait waits for the singular-controller lease to expire for all supplied
entities. (In practice, any requests that do not refer to the connection's
model will be rejected.)

Facades.Name: Spaces
Facades.Doc: API defines the methods the Spaces API facade implements.

Facades.Name: StatusHistory
Facades.Doc: API is the concrete implementation of the Pruner endpoint..

Methods.Name: Prune
Methods.Doc:
Prune endpoint removes status history entries until
only the ones newer than now - p.MaxHistoryTime remain and
the history is smaller than p.MaxHistoryMB.

Facades.Name: Storage
Facades.Doc:
API implements the storage interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: AddToUnit
Methods.Doc:
AddToUnit validates and creates additional storage instances for units.
This method handles bulk add operations and
a failure on one individual storage instance does not block remaining
instances from being processed.
A "CHANGE" block can block this operation.

Methods.Name: CreatePool
Methods.Doc: CreatePool creates a new pool with specified parameters.

Methods.Name: ListFilesystems
Methods.Doc:
ListFilesystems returns a list of filesystems in the environment matching
the provided filter. Each result describes a filesystem in detail, including
the filesystem's attachments.

Methods.Name: ListPools
Methods.Doc:
ListPools returns a list of pools.
If filter is provided, returned list only contains pools that match
the filter.
Pools can be filtered on names and provider types.
If both names and types are provided as filter,
pools that match either are returned.
This method lists union of pools and environment provider types.
If no filter is provided, all pools are returned.

Methods.Name: ListStorageDetails
Methods.Doc: ListStorageDetails returns storage matching a filter.

Methods.Name: ListVolumes
Methods.Doc:
ListVolumes lists volumes with the given filters. Each filter produces
an independent list of volumes, or an error if the filter is invalid
or the volumes could not be listed.

Methods.Name: StorageDetails
Methods.Doc:
StorageDetails retrieves and returns detailed information about desired
storage identified by supplied tags. If specified storage cannot be
retrieved, individual error is returned instead of storage information.

Facades.Name: StorageProvisioner
Facades.Doc: StorageProvisionerAPI provides access to the Provisioner API facade.

Methods.Name: AttachmentLife
Methods.Doc:
AttachmentLife returns the lifecycle state of each specified machine
storage attachment.

Methods.Name: ControllerConfig
Methods.Doc: ControllerConfig returns the controller's configuration.

Methods.Name: EnsureDead
Methods.Doc:
EnsureDead calls EnsureDead on each given entity from state. It
will fail if the entity is not present. If it's Alive, nothing will
happen (see state/EnsureDead() for units or machines).

Methods.Name: FilesystemAttachmentParams
Methods.Doc:
FilesystemAttachmentParams returns the parameters for creating the filesystem
attachments with the specified IDs.

Methods.Name: FilesystemAttachments
Methods.Doc: FilesystemAttachments returns details of filesystem attachments with the specified IDs.

Methods.Name: FilesystemParams
Methods.Doc:
FilesystemParams returns the parameters for creating the filesystems
with the specified tags.

Methods.Name: Filesystems
Methods.Doc: Filesystems returns details of filesystems with the specified tags.

Methods.Name: InstanceId
Methods.Doc:
InstanceId returns the provider specific instance id for each given
machine or an CodeNotProvisioned error, if not set.

Methods.Name: Life
Methods.Doc: Life returns the life status of every supplied entity, where available.

Methods.Name: ModelConfig
Methods.Doc: ModelConfig returns the current environment's configuration.

Methods.Name: Remove
Methods.Doc: Remove removes volumes and filesystems from state.

Methods.Name: RemoveAttachment
Methods.Doc:
RemoveAttachments removes the specified machine storage attachments
from state.

Methods.Name: SetFilesystemAttachmentInfo
Methods.Doc:
SetFilesystemAttachmentInfo records the details of newly provisioned filesystem
attachments.

Methods.Name: SetFilesystemInfo
Methods.Doc: SetFilesystemInfo records the details of newly provisioned filesystems.

Methods.Name: SetStatus
Methods.Doc: SetStatus sets the status of each given entity.

Methods.Name: SetVolumeAttachmentInfo
Methods.Doc:
SetVolumeAttachmentInfo records the details of newly provisioned volume
attachments.

Methods.Name: SetVolumeInfo
Methods.Doc: SetVolumeInfo records the details of newly provisioned volumes.

Methods.Name: UpdateStatus
Methods.Doc:
UpdateStatus updates the status data of each given entity.
TODO(fwereade): WTF. This method exists *only* for the convenience of the
*client* API -- and is itself completely broken -- but we still expose it
in every facade with a StatusSetter? FFS.

Methods.Name: VolumeAttachmentParams
Methods.Doc:
VolumeAttachmentParams returns the parameters for creating the volume
attachments with the specified IDs.

Methods.Name: VolumeAttachments
Methods.Doc: VolumeAttachments returns details of volume attachments with the specified IDs.

Methods.Name: VolumeBlockDevices
Methods.Doc:
VolumeBlockDevices returns details of the block devices corresponding to the
volume attachments with the specified IDs.

Methods.Name: VolumeParams
Methods.Doc:
VolumeParams returns the parameters for creating or destroying
the volumes with the specified tags.

Methods.Name: Volumes
Methods.Doc: Volumes returns details of volumes with the specified tags.

Methods.Name: WatchBlockDevices
Methods.Doc: WatchBlockDevices watches for changes to the specified machines' block devices.

Methods.Name: WatchFilesystemAttachments
Methods.Doc:
WatchFilesystemAttachments watches for changes to filesystem attachments
scoped to the entity with the tag passed to NewState.

Methods.Name: WatchFilesystems
Methods.Doc:
WatchFilesystems watches for changes to filesystems scoped
to the entity with the tag passed to NewState.

Methods.Name: WatchForModelConfigChanges
Methods.Doc:
WatchForModelConfigChanges returns a NotifyWatcher that observes
changes to the environment configuration.
Note that although the NotifyWatchResult contains an Error field,
it's not used because we are only returning a single watcher,
so we use the regular error return.

Methods.Name: WatchMachines
Methods.Doc: WatchMachines watches for changes to the specified machines.

Methods.Name: WatchVolumeAttachments
Methods.Doc:
WatchVolumeAttachments watches for changes to volume attachments scoped to
the entity with the tag passed to NewState.

Methods.Name: WatchVolumes
Methods.Doc:
WatchVolumes watches for changes to volumes scoped to the
entity with the tag passed to NewState.

Facades.Name: StringsWatcher
Facades.Doc:
srvStringsWatcher defines the API for methods on a state.StringsWatcher.
Each client has its own current set of watchers, stored in resources.
srvStringsWatcher notifies about changes for all entities of a given kind,
sending the changes as a list of strings.

Methods.Name: Next
Methods.Doc:
Next returns when a change has occured to an entity of the
collection being watched since the most recent call to Next
or the Watch call that created the srvStringsWatcher.

Methods.Name: Stop
Methods.Doc: Stop stops the watcher.

Facades.Name: Subnets
Facades.Doc: SubnetsAPI defines the methods the Subnets API facade implements.

Methods.Name: AddSubnets
Methods.Doc: AddSubnets adds existing subnets to Juju.

Methods.Name: AllSpaces
Methods.Doc: AllSpaces returns the tags of all network spaces known to Juju.

Methods.Name: AllZones
Methods.Doc:
AllZones returns all availability zones known to Juju. If a
zone is unusable, unavailable, or deprecated the Available
field will be false.

Methods.Name: ListSubnets
Methods.Doc:
ListSubnets returns the matching subnets after applying
optional filters.

Facades.Name: Undertaker
Facades.Doc: UndertakerAPI implements the API used by the machine undertaker worker.

Methods.Name: ModelConfig
Methods.Doc: ModelConfig returns the model's configuration.

Methods.Name: ModelInfo
Methods.Doc: ModelInfo returns information on the model needed by the undertaker worker.

Methods.Name: ProcessDyingModel
Methods.Doc:
ProcessDyingModel checks if a dying environment has any machines or services.
If there are none, the environment's life is changed from dying to dead.

Methods.Name: RemoveModel
Methods.Doc: RemoveModel removes any records of this model from Juju.

Methods.Name: SetStatus
Methods.Doc: SetStatus sets the status of each given entity.

Methods.Name: UpdateStatus
Methods.Doc:
UpdateStatus updates the status data of each given entity.
TODO(fwereade): WTF. This method exists *only* for the convenience of the
*client* API -- and is itself completely broken -- but we still expose it
in every facade with a StatusSetter? FFS.

Methods.Name: WatchModelResources
Methods.Doc:
WatchModelResources creates watchers for changes to the lifecycle of an
model's machines and services.

Facades.Name: UnitAssigner
Facades.Doc: API implements the functionality for assigning units to machines.

Methods.Name: AssignUnits
Methods.Doc:
AssignUnits assigns the units with the given ids to the correct machine. The
 error results are returned in the same order as the given entities.

Methods.Name: SetAgentStatus
Methods.Doc:
SetAgentStatus will set status for agents of Units passed in args, if one
of the args is not an Unit it will fail.

Methods.Name: WatchUnitAssignments
Methods.Doc:
WatchUnitAssignments returns a strings watcher that is notified when new unit
assignments are added to the db.

Facades.Name: Uniter
Facades.Doc: UniterAPIV3 implements the API version 3, used by the uniter worker.

Methods.Name: APIAddresses
Methods.Doc: APIAddresses returns the list of addresses used to connect to the API.

Methods.Name: APIHostPorts
Methods.Doc: APIHostPorts returns the API server addresses.

Methods.Name: Actions
Methods.Doc:
Actions returns the Actions by Tags passed and ensures that the Unit asking
for them is the same Unit that has the Actions.

Methods.Name: AddMetricBatches
Methods.Doc: AddMetricBatches adds the metrics for the specified unit.

Methods.Name: AddUnitStorage
Methods.Doc:
AddUnitStorage validates and creates additional storage instances for units.
Failures on an individual storage instance do not block remaining
instances from being processed.

Methods.Name: AllMachinePorts
Methods.Doc:
AllMachinePorts returns all opened port ranges for each given
machine (on all networks).

Methods.Name: ApplicationStatus
Methods.Doc:
ApplicationStatus returns the status of the Applications and its workloads
if the given unit is the leader.

Methods.Name: AssignedMachine
Methods.Doc:
AssignedMachine returns the machine tag for each given unit tag, or
an error satisfying params.IsCodeNotAssigned when a unit has no
assigned machine.

Methods.Name: AvailabilityZone
Methods.Doc: AvailabilityZone returns the availability zone for each given unit, if applicable.

Methods.Name: BeginActions
Methods.Doc: BeginActions marks the actions represented by the passed in Tags as running.

Methods.Name: CACert
Methods.Doc: CACert returns the certificate used to validate the state connection.

Methods.Name: CharmArchiveSha256
Methods.Doc:
CharmArchiveSha256 returns the SHA256 digest of the charm archive
(bundle) data for each charm url in the given parameters.

Methods.Name: CharmModifiedVersion
Methods.Doc:
CharmModifiedVersion returns the most CharmModifiedVersion for all given
units or services.

Methods.Name: CharmURL
Methods.Doc: CharmURL returns the charm URL for all given units or services.

Methods.Name: ClearResolved
Methods.Doc: ClearResolved removes any resolved setting from each given unit.

Methods.Name: ClosePorts
Methods.Doc:
ClosePorts sets the policy of the port range with protocol to be
closed, for all given units.

Methods.Name: ConfigSettings
Methods.Doc:
ConfigSettings returns the complete set of service charm config
settings available to each given unit.

Methods.Name: ControllerConfig
Methods.Doc: ControllerConfig returns the controller's configuration.

Methods.Name: CurrentModel
Methods.Doc: CurrentModel returns the name and UUID for the current juju model.

Methods.Name: Destroy
Methods.Doc:
Destroy advances all given Alive units' lifecycles as far as
possible. See state/Unit.Destroy().

Methods.Name: DestroyAllSubordinates
Methods.Doc: DestroyAllSubordinates destroys all subordinates of each given unit.

Methods.Name: DestroyUnitStorageAttachments
Methods.Doc:
DestroyUnitStorageAttachments marks each storage attachment of the
specified units as Dying.

Methods.Name: EnsureDead
Methods.Doc:
EnsureDead calls EnsureDead on each given entity from state. It
will fail if the entity is not present. If it's Alive, nothing will
happen (see state/EnsureDead() for units or machines).

Methods.Name: EnterScope
Methods.Doc:
EnterScope ensures each unit has entered its scope in the relation,
for all of the given relation/unit pairs. See also
state.RelationUnit.EnterScope().

Methods.Name: FinishActions
Methods.Doc: FinishActions saves the result of a completed Action

Methods.Name: GetPrincipal
Methods.Doc:
GetPrincipal returns the result of calling PrincipalName() and
converting it to a tag, on each given unit.

Methods.Name: HasSubordinates
Methods.Doc: HasSubordinates returns the whether each given unit has any subordinates.

Methods.Name: JoinedRelations
Methods.Doc:
JoinedRelations returns the tags of all relations for which each supplied unit
has entered scope. It should be called RelationsInScope, but it's not convenient
to make that change until we have versioned APIs.

Methods.Name: LeaveScope
Methods.Doc:
LeaveScope signals each unit has left its scope in the relation,
for all of the given relation/unit pairs. See also
state.RelationUnit.LeaveScope().

Methods.Name: Life
Methods.Doc: Life returns the life status of every supplied entity, where available.

Methods.Name: Merge
Methods.Doc:
Merge merges in the provided leadership settings. Only leaders for
the given service may perform this operation.

Methods.Name: ModelConfig
Methods.Doc: ModelConfig returns the current environment's configuration.

Methods.Name: ModelUUID
Methods.Doc:
ModelUUID returns the model UUID to connect to the environment
that the current connection is for.

Methods.Name: NetworkConfig
Methods.Doc:
NetworkConfig returns information about all given relation/unit pairs,
including their id, key and the local endpoint.

Methods.Name: OpenPorts
Methods.Doc:
OpenPorts sets the policy of the port range with protocol to be
opened, for all given units.

Methods.Name: PrivateAddress
Methods.Doc: PrivateAddress returns the private address for each given unit, if set.

Methods.Name: ProviderType
Methods.Doc:
ProviderType returns the provider type used by the current juju
model.

TODO(dimitern): Refactor the uniter to call this instead of calling
ModelConfig() just to get the provider type. Once we have machine
addresses, this might be completely unnecessary though.

Methods.Name: PublicAddress
Methods.Doc: PublicAddress returns the public address for each given unit, if set.

Methods.Name: Read
Methods.Doc:
Read reads leadership settings for the provided service ID. Any
unit of the service may perform this operation.

Methods.Name: ReadRemoteSettings
Methods.Doc:
ReadRemoteSettings returns the remote settings of each given set of
relation/local unit/remote unit.

Methods.Name: ReadSettings
Methods.Doc:
ReadSettings returns the local settings of each given set of
relation/unit.

Methods.Name: Relation
Methods.Doc:
Relation returns information about all given relation/unit pairs,
including their id, key and the local endpoint.

Methods.Name: RelationById
Methods.Doc:
RelationById returns information about all given relations,
specified by their ids, including their key and the local
endpoint.

Methods.Name: RemoveStorageAttachments
Methods.Doc:
RemoveStorageAttachments removes the specified storage
attachments from state.

Methods.Name: RequestReboot
Methods.Doc: RequestReboot sets the reboot flag on the provided machines

Methods.Name: Resolved
Methods.Doc: Resolved returns the current resolved setting for each given unit.

Methods.Name: SetAgentStatus
Methods.Doc:
SetAgentStatus will set status for agents of Units passed in args, if one
of the args is not an Unit it will fail.

Methods.Name: SetApplicationStatus
Methods.Doc:
SetApplicationStatus sets the status for all the Services in args if the given Unit is
the leader.

Methods.Name: SetCharmURL
Methods.Doc:
SetCharmURL sets the charm URL for each given unit. An error will
be returned if a unit is dead, or the charm URL is not know.

Methods.Name: SetStatus
Methods.Doc:
SetStatus will set status for a entities passed in args. If the entity is
a Unit it will instead set status to its agent, to emulate backwards
compatibility.

Methods.Name: SetUnitStatus
Methods.Doc:
SetUnitStatus sets status for all elements passed in args, the difference
with SetStatus is that if an entity is a Unit it will set its status instead
of its agent.

Methods.Name: StorageAttachmentLife
Methods.Doc:
StorageAttachmentLife returns the lifecycle state of the storage attachments
with the specified tags.

Methods.Name: StorageAttachments
Methods.Doc: StorageAttachments returns the storage attachments with the specified tags.

Methods.Name: UnitStatus
Methods.Doc: UnitStatus returns the workload status information for the unit.

Methods.Name: UnitStorageAttachments
Methods.Doc: UnitStorageAttachments returns the IDs of storage attachments for a collection of units.

Methods.Name: UpdateSettings
Methods.Doc:
UpdateSettings persists all changes made to the local settings of
all given pairs of relation and unit. Keys with empty values are
considered a signal to delete these values.

Methods.Name: Watch
Methods.Doc: Watch starts an NotifyWatcher for each given entity.

Methods.Name: WatchAPIHostPorts
Methods.Doc: WatchAPIHostPorts watches the API server addresses.

Methods.Name: WatchActionNotifications
Methods.Doc:
WatchActionNotifications returns a StringsWatcher for observing
incoming action calls to a unit. See also state/watcher.go
Unit.WatchActionNotifications(). This method is called from
api/uniter/uniter.go WatchActionNotifications().

Methods.Name: WatchApplicationRelations
Methods.Doc:
WatchApplicationRelations returns a StringsWatcher, for each given
service, that notifies of changes to the lifecycles of relations
involving that service.

Methods.Name: WatchConfigSettings
Methods.Doc:
WatchConfigSettings returns a NotifyWatcher for observing changes
to each unit's service configuration settings. See also
state/watcher.go:Unit.WatchConfigSettings().

Methods.Name: WatchForModelConfigChanges
Methods.Doc:
WatchForModelConfigChanges returns a NotifyWatcher that observes
changes to the environment configuration.
Note that although the NotifyWatchResult contains an Error field,
it's not used because we are only returning a single watcher,
so we use the regular error return.

Methods.Name: WatchLeadershipSettings
Methods.Doc:
WatchLeadershipSettings will block the caller until leadership settings
for the given service ID change.

Methods.Name: WatchRelationUnits
Methods.Doc:
WatchRelationUnits returns a RelationUnitsWatcher for observing
changes to every unit in the supplied relation that is visible to
the supplied unit. See also state/watcher.go:RelationUnit.Watch().

Methods.Name: WatchStorageAttachments
Methods.Doc:
WatchStorageAttachments creates watchers for a collection of storage
attachments, each of which can be used to watch changes to storage
attachment info.

Methods.Name: WatchUnitAddresses
Methods.Doc:
WatchUnitAddresses returns a NotifyWatcher for observing changes
to each unit's addresses.

Methods.Name: WatchUnitStorageAttachments
Methods.Doc:
WatchUnitStorageAttachments creates watchers for a collection of units,
each of which can be used to watch for lifecycle changes to the corresponding
unit's storage attachments.

Facades.Name: UserManager
Facades.Doc:
UserManagerAPI implements the user manager interface and is the concrete
implementation of the api end point.

Methods.Name: AddUser
Methods.Doc:
AddUser adds a user with a username, and either a password or
a randomly generated secret key which will be returned.

Methods.Name: CreateLocalLoginMacaroon
Methods.Doc:
CreateLocalLoginMacaroon creates a macaroon for the specified users to use
for future logins.

Methods.Name: DisableUser
Methods.Doc:
DisableUser disables one or more users.  If the user is already disabled,
the action is consided a success.

Methods.Name: EnableUser
Methods.Doc:
EnableUser enables one or more users.  If the user is already enabled,
the action is consided a success.

Methods.Name: SetPassword
Methods.Doc: SetPassword changes the stored password for the specified users.

Methods.Name: UserInfo
Methods.Doc: UserInfo returns information on a user.

Facades.Name: VolumeAttachmentsWatcher
Facades.Doc:
srvMachineStorageIdsWatcher defines the API wrapping a state.StringsWatcher
watching machine/storage attachments. This watcher notifies about storage
entities (volumes/filesystems) being attached to and detached from machines.

TODO(axw) state needs a new watcher, this is a bt of a hack. State watchers
could do with some deduplication of logic, and I don't want to add to that
spaghetti right now.

Methods.Name: Next
Methods.Doc:
Next returns when a change has occured to an entity of the
collection being watched since the most recent call to Next
or the Watch call that created the srvMachineStorageIdsWatcher.

Methods.Name: Stop
Methods.Doc: Stop stops the watcher.

Methods.Name: Login
Methods.Doc:
Login logs in with the provided credentials.  All subsequent requests on the
connection will act as the authenticated user.
